# Postgres Rules

## Hybrid data model

- Firebase Auth → `users.firebase_uid`
- Postgres owns: `users`, `user_preferences`, `places` (snapshots), `favorites`, `groups`, `group_members`, `group_favorites`, `group_invites`

## Place storage

Store only interacted OSM places (favorited or group-saved). Do not mirror full Overpass dataset.

```sql
-- place id format: node/12345, way/67890
primary key (user_id, place_id) on favorites
primary key (group_id, user_id) on group_members
```

## Migrations

- Versioned SQL in `db/migrations/`
- Phase 1 tables first: users, places, favorites, groups, group_members
- Phase 2+: group_favorites, group_invites, reviews, activities

## Queries

- Filter by authenticated `user_id` or verified group membership
- Add indexes before shipping list endpoints
- Use transactions for group creation (group + owner membership)

## Env

- `DATABASE_URL` is server-only — never expose in client bundle
